1
00:00:13,733 --> 00:00:14,967
<i> Any update, bro?</i>

2
00:00:15,100 --> 00:00:16,867
<i>Yeah. Nothing.
I've been asking around, too.</i>

3
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:18,733
<i> Should we tell the kids?</i>

4
00:00:18,867 --> 00:00:21,833
<i>Why did Mom leave
without telling anyone?</i>

5
00:00:21,967 --> 00:00:23,433
<i>And if Hazel really has nothing
to do with it,</i>

6
00:00:23,567 --> 00:00:24,800
<i>why would she disappear
without us knowing?</i>

7
00:00:24,933 --> 00:00:26,633
<i> Your mom is sick.</i>

8
00:00:26,767 --> 00:00:28,067
<i> She has a brain tumor.</i>

9
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:32,133
<i>What if Hazel found out
about Mom's condition?</i>

10
00:00:32,267 --> 00:00:33,933
<i> And took advantage of it?</i>

11
00:00:34,100 --> 00:00:35,133
<i> I'm coming!</i>

12
00:00:37,467 --> 00:00:39,467
<i> Manuel.</i>

13
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:40,500
<i> Is he here?</i>

14
00:00:40,633 --> 00:00:42,200
<i> I got a lead.</i>

15
00:00:42,333 --> 00:00:43,733
<i> I know where your mom is.</i>

16
00:01:05,067 --> 00:01:06,267
Yes, Sir.

17
00:01:06,400 --> 00:01:07,300
I remember now.

18
00:01:07,467 --> 00:01:09,600
She's the woman
who rode my taxi.

19
00:01:09,733 --> 00:01:11,467
The one I argued with yesterday.

20
00:01:11,600 --> 00:01:14,400
What? Why, Mister?
What happened?

21
00:01:14,533 --> 00:01:17,633
We were already about five
kilometers in when suddenly...

22
00:01:17,767 --> 00:01:18,967
<i> Mister?</i>

23
00:01:19,100 --> 00:01:21,000
<i> Where are we?</i>

24
00:01:21,133 --> 00:01:23,000
<i> This is way too far from FMP.</i>

25
00:01:24,500 --> 00:01:26,667
<i> Ma'am, what's FMP?</i>

26
00:01:26,800 --> 00:01:28,533
<i> That place! FMP!</i>

27
00:01:28,667 --> 00:01:31,267
<i> Just take me there.</i>

28
00:01:31,400 --> 00:01:33,533
<i>Ma'am, you told me earlier
to bring you to the airport.</i>

29
00:01:33,667 --> 00:01:35,767
<i> What? Airport?</i>

30
00:01:35,900 --> 00:01:37,533
<i> Why would I go there?</i>

31
00:01:37,667 --> 00:01:40,233
<i> Mister, you're scamming me.</i>

32
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:41,633
<i> Don't mess with me.</i>

33
00:01:41,767 --> 00:01:43,667
<i> I know all those tricks.</i>

34
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:45,533
<i> Pull over!</i>

35
00:01:45,667 --> 00:01:48,300
<i> Stop the car! Stop it, Mister!</i>

36
00:01:50,933 --> 00:01:52,667
<i>Ma'am, are you already
getting off?</i>

37
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:54,033
<i> Ma'am, your fare!</i>

38
00:01:54,167 --> 00:01:55,567
<i> You scammed me.</i>

39
00:01:55,700 --> 00:01:56,933
<i> Wait, Ma'am! Your payment!</i>

40
00:01:57,067 --> 00:01:59,100
<i> No!</i>

41
00:01:59,233 --> 00:02:00,633
<i>- Your fare!
- This is my umbrella!</i>

42
00:02:00,767 --> 00:02:02,700
<i> You even took my umbrella!</i>

43
00:02:02,833 --> 00:02:05,367
The meter already hit 185.

44
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:07,167
At first, I thought
I was the one being scammed,

45
00:02:07,300 --> 00:02:09,733
but she didn't really look
like that kind of person.

46
00:02:09,867 --> 00:02:11,533
Is that so?

47
00:02:11,667 --> 00:02:14,567
Sorry about that, bro.
She's sick.

48
00:02:14,733 --> 00:02:15,967
I guess this would be enough.

49
00:02:16,100 --> 00:02:17,767
Oh, I'm sorry.

50
00:02:17,900 --> 00:02:18,900
I didn't notice.

51
00:02:19,033 --> 00:02:22,100
I wish I'd taken her
to that FMP place.

52
00:02:22,233 --> 00:02:24,333
It's okay, Mister.
Thank you so much.

53
00:02:24,467 --> 00:02:26,667
- Alright.
- Thank you.

54
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:28,600
Take care.

55
00:02:28,733 --> 00:02:30,900
Where did Mom go?

56
00:02:31,033 --> 00:02:32,700
Do you think she went back
to Davao?

57
00:02:32,833 --> 00:02:34,533
Maybe that's the last thing
she remembers.

58
00:02:34,667 --> 00:02:36,333
She's in Davao.

59
00:02:36,467 --> 00:02:38,900
And she asked to be dropped off
at the airport, right?

60
00:02:39,033 --> 00:02:42,700
Could be.
She had her bag with her.

61
00:02:42,833 --> 00:02:45,967
She always keeps cash
in that bag. Her cards, too.

62
00:02:46,100 --> 00:02:48,633
She might've booked a flight.

63
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:50,867
I thought of that, too.

64
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:53,567
So I called Manang Lucy...

65
00:02:53,700 --> 00:02:54,633
and Emil.

66
00:02:55,900 --> 00:02:57,633
But she wasn't there.

67
00:03:00,267 --> 00:03:02,000
So where is Mom?

68
00:03:08,267 --> 00:03:10,367
You actually took care
of your rival?

69
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:12,233
I couldn't just abandon her.

70
00:03:14,867 --> 00:03:16,033
Look at this.

71
00:03:16,167 --> 00:03:17,500
Read it.

72
00:03:18,767 --> 00:03:21,233
This is for brain swelling.

73
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:23,133
And anti-epileptics.

74
00:03:24,100 --> 00:03:25,433
Is Felma sick?

75
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:29,567
Apparently.

76
00:03:29,700 --> 00:03:33,267
And if she doesn't recognize me,
that means it's already bad.

77
00:03:34,333 --> 00:03:35,633
<i> So you really are sick?</i>

78
00:03:36,767 --> 00:03:38,033
<i> Cancer?</i>

79
00:03:38,167 --> 00:03:39,633
<i> Stage four.</i>

80
00:03:39,767 --> 00:03:41,033
<i> Really?</i>

81
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:45,133
<i> I'm not sick.</i>

82
00:03:45,267 --> 00:03:47,733
That woman really fooled me.

83
00:03:47,867 --> 00:03:49,600
So she really is sick.

84
00:03:51,767 --> 00:03:53,800
I actually hope
it's brain cancer.

85
00:03:53,967 --> 00:03:56,067
And I hope it's stage four.

86
00:03:56,200 --> 00:03:57,533
Hazel, come on.

87
00:03:58,867 --> 00:04:01,833
I don't trust that laugh at all.

88
00:04:01,967 --> 00:04:04,467
Are you plotting
something again?

89
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:06,633
You know, I was just thinking.

90
00:04:06,767 --> 00:04:10,567
My husband's mistress
treats me like a friend.

91
00:04:10,700 --> 00:04:12,833
So what if...

92
00:04:12,967 --> 00:04:14,267
I help her?

93
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:15,700
Pretend.

94
00:04:17,533 --> 00:04:19,633
I'll take her to the hospital.

95
00:04:19,767 --> 00:04:22,567
Of course, her
family will thank me.

96
00:04:22,700 --> 00:04:25,433
They'll owe me.

97
00:04:25,567 --> 00:04:28,300
I'll volunteer
to be her personal nurse.

98
00:04:28,467 --> 00:04:30,200
I'm sure they won't refuse.

99
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:35,367
Hazel, are you really
doing this?

100
00:04:37,567 --> 00:04:40,233
I'll be the best caregiver

101
00:04:40,367 --> 00:04:43,200
while I win over Manuel
and his kids.

102
00:04:44,267 --> 00:04:47,067
So when Felma dies,

103
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:50,567
it'll be easy for me to enter
their family.

104
00:04:50,700 --> 00:04:52,000
Happy family.

105
00:04:57,433 --> 00:04:58,400
Felma's awake. Hide for now.

106
00:04:58,533 --> 00:05:00,100
Her memory might get triggered
if she sees you.

107
00:05:00,233 --> 00:05:01,467
Even me.

108
00:05:01,633 --> 00:05:02,767
- Go.
- Andrea.

109
00:05:04,133 --> 00:05:05,467
Coleen.

110
00:05:08,100 --> 00:05:09,533
Jeffrey.

111
00:05:09,667 --> 00:05:11,367
Andrea.

112
00:05:12,733 --> 00:05:14,067
Coleen.

113
00:05:18,533 --> 00:05:19,833
Jeffrey...

114
00:05:20,967 --> 00:05:22,333
Jeffrey.

115
00:05:25,967 --> 00:05:27,933
Coleen?

116
00:05:28,067 --> 00:05:29,700
Andrea?

117
00:05:32,233 --> 00:05:33,600
Jeffrey?

118
00:05:35,367 --> 00:05:36,967
- Andrea...
- Felma.

119
00:05:37,100 --> 00:05:38,033
Friend.

120
00:05:40,633 --> 00:05:42,733
How are you feeling?

121
00:05:42,867 --> 00:05:44,600
Does your head still hurt?

122
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:48,033
Just tell me, okay?

123
00:05:48,167 --> 00:05:49,867
So I can get rid of you.

124
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:51,500
Okay?

125
00:05:52,933 --> 00:05:54,733
I can get rid of it.

126
00:06:14,433 --> 00:06:15,667
Thank you.

127
00:06:19,300 --> 00:06:21,367
You are...

128
00:06:21,500 --> 00:06:22,800
I'm Hazel.

129
00:06:24,233 --> 00:06:25,533
But...

130
00:06:26,900 --> 00:06:29,467
we call each other "friend".

131
00:06:35,333 --> 00:06:37,433
Sorry, friend.

132
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:41,833
There's so much
I can't remember.

133
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:43,367
But...

134
00:06:44,467 --> 00:06:47,467
we must be close.

135
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:49,400
Because...

136
00:06:49,533 --> 00:06:54,933
I didn't even realize how
I ended up here in your place.

137
00:06:55,067 --> 00:06:56,733
My feet just brought me here.

138
00:06:56,867 --> 00:06:57,967
Of course.

139
00:06:58,967 --> 00:07:00,700
We're best friends.

140
00:07:02,067 --> 00:07:04,300
Maybe...

141
00:07:04,433 --> 00:07:07,233
your feet brought you here

142
00:07:07,367 --> 00:07:09,000
because that's what
your heart wanted.

143
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:15,567
I hope I remember you someday.

144
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:19,167
Help me remember.

145
00:07:21,233 --> 00:07:24,733
Tell me when and how we met.

146
00:07:26,700 --> 00:07:28,400
We met when...

147
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:32,333
my husband left me.

148
00:07:34,067 --> 00:07:35,867
And another woman stole him.

149
00:07:48,367 --> 00:07:51,467
Sir, my mother has been
missing for over 24 hours.

150
00:07:53,700 --> 00:07:56,633
We're having a hard time
finding her because...

151
00:07:56,767 --> 00:07:58,500
she's sick.

152
00:07:59,467 --> 00:08:01,567
Sir, please help us.

153
00:08:02,667 --> 00:08:05,133
Yes, Ma'am.
This has already been reported.

154
00:08:05,267 --> 00:08:08,000
In fact, the chief
already instructed us

155
00:08:08,133 --> 00:08:10,667
to coordinate
with other precincts.

156
00:08:12,900 --> 00:08:14,667
Thank you so much, Sir.

157
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:16,067
Alright, Sir and Ma'am.

158
00:08:16,200 --> 00:08:18,300
We'll take care of this.
Please don't worry.

159
00:08:18,433 --> 00:08:19,567
- Okay.
- Sir, please find her.

160
00:08:19,700 --> 00:08:21,033
- We will.
- Thank you.

161
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:22,900
Joel, let's go.

162
00:08:26,333 --> 00:08:28,067
We met at a...

163
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:30,300
church.

164
00:08:31,767 --> 00:08:34,233
You saw me...

165
00:08:34,367 --> 00:08:35,733
crying.

166
00:08:36,833 --> 00:08:38,433
So...

167
00:08:38,567 --> 00:08:40,067
you came up to me.

168
00:08:41,033 --> 00:08:42,700
You talked to me.

169
00:08:42,833 --> 00:08:44,133
And the rest is history.

170
00:08:45,233 --> 00:08:46,600
Our story.

171
00:08:48,967 --> 00:08:51,500
I hope I was able to help you

172
00:08:51,633 --> 00:08:53,667
through what you went through
in life.

173
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:58,233
I hope I was a good friend.

174
00:09:01,400 --> 00:09:03,200
Did you forgive your husband?

175
00:09:05,100 --> 00:09:06,467
I love my husband.

176
00:09:07,867 --> 00:09:09,567
So I can forgive him.

177
00:09:10,933 --> 00:09:13,433
But the one
I will never forgive...

178
00:09:14,500 --> 00:09:16,600
is the woman who stole him.

179
00:09:20,433 --> 00:09:22,167
That explains it.

180
00:09:23,267 --> 00:09:25,833
I can see the sadness
in your eyes.

181
00:09:26,833 --> 00:09:28,633
That...

182
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:31,233
deep anger in your heart.

183
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:34,400
Forgive her, friend.

184
00:09:34,533 --> 00:09:35,467
No.

185
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:36,433
You ruined...

186
00:09:36,567 --> 00:09:38,300
She ruined my life.

187
00:09:39,300 --> 00:09:41,433
Did she ruin your life?

188
00:09:41,567 --> 00:09:43,700
Or did you ruin it yourself?

189
00:09:43,833 --> 00:09:45,633
Friend...

190
00:09:45,767 --> 00:09:47,933
are you taking
my husband's mistress's side?

191
00:09:49,700 --> 00:09:51,367
No, friend.

192
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:53,267
You have every right.

193
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:57,600
She took your husband.

194
00:09:58,600 --> 00:09:59,900
But...

195
00:10:01,267 --> 00:10:07,100
it's not right to keep carrying
all that anger.

196
00:10:07,233 --> 00:10:08,967
You're the one who'll suffer.

197
00:10:10,933 --> 00:10:13,467
I love my husband.

198
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:15,667
No matter what happens,

199
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:17,967
I won't let anyone take him
from me.

200
00:10:20,267 --> 00:10:22,067
But does he still love you?

201
00:10:26,267 --> 00:10:27,833
Well if he doesn't anymore,

202
00:10:27,967 --> 00:10:29,700
let him go.

203
00:10:30,433 --> 00:10:31,800
Because...

204
00:10:34,367 --> 00:10:36,833
love yourself more.

205
00:10:36,967 --> 00:10:42,033
Don't let your happiness
depend on him.

206
00:10:42,167 --> 00:10:43,833
Remember,

207
00:10:43,967 --> 00:10:46,167
he's not the only man
in the world.

208
00:10:47,733 --> 00:10:50,233
There's someone else out
there who will love you

209
00:10:50,367 --> 00:10:52,000
honestly...

210
00:10:52,133 --> 00:10:54,700
and completely.

211
00:10:54,833 --> 00:10:57,267
But how will you ever see that

212
00:10:57,400 --> 00:10:59,600
if your heart
is filled with anger

213
00:11:00,533 --> 00:11:03,767
toward someone
who doesn't even love you?

214
00:11:13,333 --> 00:11:15,400
I forgot, friend.

215
00:11:15,533 --> 00:11:18,600
Friend, I forgot
to take my medicine.

216
00:11:18,733 --> 00:11:22,333
Friend, can you help me?

217
00:11:22,467 --> 00:11:24,100
- It's over there, the...
- Oh, okay.

218
00:11:24,233 --> 00:11:25,300
the medicine.

219
00:11:25,433 --> 00:11:27,133
I'll get your medicine.

220
00:11:28,467 --> 00:11:29,400
It hurts.

221
00:11:29,533 --> 00:11:30,600
Friend!

222
00:11:30,733 --> 00:11:31,733
Help!

223
00:11:33,500 --> 00:11:35,433
Help!

224
00:11:40,233 --> 00:11:42,000
Friend!

225
00:11:46,533 --> 00:11:47,833
Friend!

226
00:11:47,967 --> 00:11:49,167
Help!

227
00:11:51,867 --> 00:11:54,867
Friend, what are you supposed
to give her?

228
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:57,467
You've already thrown away
her medicines.

229
00:11:59,967 --> 00:12:01,333
Nothing then.

230
00:12:01,467 --> 00:12:03,933
Hazel, what are you doing?

231
00:12:04,067 --> 00:12:06,433
I'm taking her
to the hospital anyway.

232
00:12:06,567 --> 00:12:08,233
But let her suffer for now.

233
00:12:21,033 --> 00:12:22,200
So what now?

234
00:12:22,333 --> 00:12:25,200
We just wait
for the police to call?

235
00:12:25,333 --> 00:12:27,867
What else can we do, Coleen?

236
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:31,300
Just pray they find
your mom soon.

237
00:12:31,433 --> 00:12:32,667
Or...

238
00:12:32,800 --> 00:12:36,000
we could call my relative
who's a medium.

239
00:12:36,133 --> 00:12:37,267
Right?

240
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:39,533
You know, Didang...

241
00:12:39,667 --> 00:12:41,267
- Fine. Go ahead, contact her.
- Dad?

242
00:12:41,400 --> 00:12:43,033
Dad's here, sis.

243
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:45,633
Dad.

244
00:12:48,567 --> 00:12:50,967
Uncle Manuel,
how is it? Any news?

245
00:12:51,100 --> 00:12:52,833
We checked everywhere
she might've gone.

246
00:12:52,967 --> 00:12:54,667
Even the place we used to rent.

247
00:12:54,800 --> 00:12:56,467
We thought
she might've gone there.

248
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:58,433
But no, she never showed up.

249
00:13:05,267 --> 00:13:06,600
Hello?

250
00:13:07,667 --> 00:13:09,433
Yes, Dr. Rosario.

251
00:13:11,200 --> 00:13:12,867
What?

252
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:14,767
Felma's at
Southcrest Hospital?

253
00:13:15,767 --> 00:13:16,967
Alright.

254
00:13:17,100 --> 00:13:18,733
We're on our way.

255
00:13:18,867 --> 00:13:20,000
- She's at Southcrest?
- Yes.

256
00:13:20,133 --> 00:13:22,200
- Come on, let's go.
- Why is she there?

257
00:13:22,367 --> 00:13:23,767
Uncle Noah, what did they say.

258
00:13:23,900 --> 00:13:25,167
Didang, please
wait here for now.

259
00:13:25,300 --> 00:13:26,733
Be careful.

260
00:13:29,967 --> 00:13:32,100
Ma'am, how are you feeling?

261
00:13:38,100 --> 00:13:38,933
Mom?

262
00:13:39,067 --> 00:13:42,267
- Miss Felma. You have visitors.
- Mom.

263
00:13:43,367 --> 00:13:44,600
Mom.

264
00:13:54,133 --> 00:13:55,267
Manuel.

265
00:13:59,900 --> 00:14:01,033
Noah.

266
00:14:08,133 --> 00:14:09,300
Jeffrey.

267
00:14:12,667 --> 00:14:13,900
Coleen.

268
00:14:20,400 --> 00:14:21,600
Andrea.

269
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:24,867
My dear children.

270
00:14:27,233 --> 00:14:29,633
I got really
scared there, Mom.

271
00:14:29,800 --> 00:14:31,933
I thought you'd forgotten us.

272
00:14:33,367 --> 00:14:35,433
What?

273
00:14:35,567 --> 00:14:38,233
Why would I forget you?

274
00:14:44,767 --> 00:14:46,100
Mom, we already know.

275
00:14:47,867 --> 00:14:49,533
We were told...

276
00:14:51,867 --> 00:14:53,600
you have a brain tumor?

277
00:14:59,133 --> 00:15:00,400
Noah,

278
00:15:02,833 --> 00:15:05,300
why did you tell them?

279
00:15:05,433 --> 00:15:07,433
Didn't we agree to wait?

280
00:15:07,567 --> 00:15:08,867
Not this time yet.

281
00:15:11,433 --> 00:15:14,033
Noah didn't say anything.

282
00:15:14,167 --> 00:15:16,700
I only found out when I followed
you to Davao.

283
00:15:18,533 --> 00:15:19,667
Davao?

284
00:15:22,833 --> 00:15:24,233
Why were we in Davao?

285
00:15:28,667 --> 00:15:30,933
I don't remember much.

286
00:15:32,400 --> 00:15:33,633
Mom?

287
00:15:33,767 --> 00:15:35,600
Mom?

288
00:15:35,767 --> 00:15:38,167
Mom, just relax.

289
00:15:38,300 --> 00:15:42,667
The doctor said that's really an
effect of your brain tumor.

290
00:15:44,033 --> 00:15:48,167
You are experiencing some
memory loss, Miss Felma.

291
00:15:48,300 --> 00:15:51,567
That's normal with a
frontal lobe meningioma.

292
00:15:51,700 --> 00:15:54,233
Some memories are clear.

293
00:15:54,367 --> 00:15:57,567
Others are
patchy or blurry.

294
00:15:57,700 --> 00:16:01,500
Some memories are even
completely blocked.

295
00:16:01,633 --> 00:16:03,300
There's no
predictable pattern.

296
00:16:03,433 --> 00:16:05,233
Doctor,

297
00:16:05,367 --> 00:16:08,233
does that mean...

298
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:10,800
I could forget my children?

299
00:16:10,933 --> 00:16:12,500
Memories can come and go,

300
00:16:12,633 --> 00:16:15,133
especially while the tumor
is still pressing

301
00:16:15,267 --> 00:16:16,833
on your frontal lobe.

302
00:16:16,967 --> 00:16:18,733
That's why we need
to avoid stress

303
00:16:18,867 --> 00:16:23,900
and not force her to remember
things she can't.

304
00:16:24,033 --> 00:16:28,000
Especially
painful memories.

305
00:16:28,133 --> 00:16:32,167
Stick to positive
and familiar ones.

306
00:16:32,300 --> 00:16:36,667
That will help stabilize
her cognitive function.

307
00:16:36,800 --> 00:16:38,900
Doctor, do you know
who brought her here?

308
00:16:39,033 --> 00:16:40,867
We just want to thank them.

309
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:42,133
I did.

310
00:16:57,433 --> 00:16:59,233
So Mom was really with you
all along!

311
00:16:59,367 --> 00:17:00,400
We've been looking for her
everywhere,

312
00:17:00,533 --> 00:17:02,733
running all over the place!

313
00:17:02,867 --> 00:17:04,967
Why did you kidnap her?

314
00:17:05,100 --> 00:17:08,467
Wait, Andrea.
What do you mean by kidnap?

315
00:17:08,600 --> 00:17:11,500
She came to my house earlier.

316
00:17:11,633 --> 00:17:12,767
She was exhausted.

317
00:17:12,900 --> 00:17:14,500
Hazel, don't mess with us!

318
00:17:14,633 --> 00:17:15,933
Jeffrey, if you don't
believe me,

319
00:17:16,100 --> 00:17:18,967
go check our neighbor's CCTV.

320
00:17:19,100 --> 00:17:20,500
When Manuel came by yesterday,

321
00:17:20,633 --> 00:17:22,933
Felma wasn't there yet.
She didn't go there.

322
00:17:23,067 --> 00:17:25,567
Who knows where you hid her?

323
00:17:28,733 --> 00:17:30,067
Kids...

324
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:34,900
why are you fighting
with my best friend?

325
00:17:37,100 --> 00:17:38,300
She helped me.

326
00:17:38,433 --> 00:17:40,533
Tell the truth!

327
00:17:40,667 --> 00:17:42,267
What did you do?
Why was Mom with you?

328
00:17:42,400 --> 00:17:43,533
Tell the truth!

329
00:17:43,667 --> 00:17:46,000
And what does Mom mean
by "best friend," huh?

330
00:17:46,133 --> 00:17:47,033
What did you do to her?

331
00:17:47,167 --> 00:17:49,200
Did you take advantage
of Mom's condition?

332
00:17:49,367 --> 00:17:50,667
You know she's weak right now.

333
00:17:50,800 --> 00:17:52,967
Why are you doing this
to our family again?

334
00:17:53,100 --> 00:17:54,033
You're messing with us.

335
00:17:54,167 --> 00:17:55,733
Don't you feel sorry
for us at all?

336
00:17:55,867 --> 00:17:57,033
Look at my mom's condition!

337
00:17:57,167 --> 00:17:58,700
Everyone, please!

338
00:17:58,833 --> 00:18:00,200
You're not helping her.

339
00:18:00,333 --> 00:18:01,533
You need to step out for now.

340
00:18:01,667 --> 00:18:03,200
This isn't good for her.

341
00:18:03,333 --> 00:18:03,967
Felma.

342
00:18:04,100 --> 00:18:05,567
Marie, Tess...

343
00:18:05,700 --> 00:18:07,033
- You are not friends.
- Please assist them.

344
00:18:07,167 --> 00:18:09,133
- You are not friends.
- Enough. That's enough.

345
00:18:09,267 --> 00:18:10,633
Tess.

346
00:18:10,767 --> 00:18:13,200
Come on, Andrea.

347
00:18:13,333 --> 00:18:14,800
What are you talking about?

348
00:18:14,933 --> 00:18:15,767
- Come on, Andrea.
- You're staying there?

349
00:18:15,900 --> 00:18:18,333
Come with us!
Who do you think you are?

350
00:18:18,467 --> 00:18:20,533
Are you really taking advantage
of our mom?

351
00:18:20,667 --> 00:18:21,567
Why are you like this?

352
00:18:21,700 --> 00:18:23,467
You always do this
to our family!

353
00:18:23,633 --> 00:18:25,733
Aren't you tired
of making us suffer?

354
00:18:25,867 --> 00:18:27,500
- Just a second.
- Tell the truth, Hazel!

355
00:18:27,633 --> 00:18:30,067
Why was Mom with you?

356
00:18:30,200 --> 00:18:33,167
Andrea, didn't you hear
what I said earlier?

357
00:18:33,300 --> 00:18:37,767
Felma came to our house.
On her own.

358
00:18:37,900 --> 00:18:38,800
Really?

359
00:18:38,933 --> 00:18:41,833
Out of everyone,
she just had to go to you?

360
00:18:41,967 --> 00:18:44,533
I don't know. I really don't.

361
00:18:44,667 --> 00:18:45,900
Maybe...

362
00:18:46,033 --> 00:18:48,033
it's because of her condition.

363
00:18:48,167 --> 00:18:50,933
Didn't the doctor tell you

364
00:18:51,067 --> 00:18:53,867
she's suffering
from inconsistent memory loss

365
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:57,367
because of her
frontal lobe meningioma?

366
00:18:58,733 --> 00:18:59,967
What is wrong with you people?

367
00:19:00,100 --> 00:19:01,800
This is unbelievable.

368
00:19:01,933 --> 00:19:04,867
You act as if you
owe me nothing.

369
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:07,100
I helped Felma, didn't I?

370
00:19:07,233 --> 00:19:09,000
And now you're angry at me?

371
00:19:10,067 --> 00:19:11,967
I should've just...

372
00:19:12,100 --> 00:19:14,133
left her at the gate.

373
00:19:14,267 --> 00:19:15,567
I shouldn't have let her in.

374
00:19:17,700 --> 00:19:19,400
Just give this to Felma.

375
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:23,733
Hey!

376
00:19:23,867 --> 00:19:25,267
Hazel!

377
00:19:27,033 --> 00:19:28,300
Dad!

378
00:19:29,600 --> 00:19:30,900
Hazel!

379
00:19:31,833 --> 00:19:33,633
Hazel, wait.

380
00:19:33,767 --> 00:19:36,600
Let's talk first, okay?

381
00:19:36,733 --> 00:19:37,833
Hazel!

382
00:19:38,867 --> 00:19:40,600
What kind of nonsense
is this now?

383
00:19:42,433 --> 00:19:44,233
Manuel, can you not?

384
00:19:44,367 --> 00:19:46,400
Your kids already
attacked me.

385
00:19:46,533 --> 00:19:47,867
Don't add to it.

386
00:19:49,600 --> 00:19:51,633
I honestly
don't understand why...

387
00:19:51,767 --> 00:19:54,200
none of you believe me.

388
00:19:54,333 --> 00:19:57,200
Because it's hard to believe
that Felma would go to you.

389
00:19:58,533 --> 00:20:01,367
Felma herself said
it, didn't she?

390
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:03,100
I saved her.

391
00:20:03,267 --> 00:20:05,300
I helped her.

392
00:20:05,433 --> 00:20:07,500
She came to me willingly.

393
00:20:08,933 --> 00:20:11,800
Now I don't know...

394
00:20:11,933 --> 00:20:14,033
how or why.

395
00:20:15,767 --> 00:20:17,433
But if I had bad intentions,

396
00:20:19,167 --> 00:20:20,867
I wouldn't have brought her
to the hospital.

397
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:24,300
Manuel,

398
00:20:24,433 --> 00:20:26,167
yes, I'm angry at Felma.

399
00:20:27,867 --> 00:20:29,200
I'm angry at her...

400
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:31,867
because she's your mistress.

401
00:20:33,333 --> 00:20:35,067
She's my enemy.

402
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:36,533
But I'm also a nurse.

403
00:20:38,467 --> 00:20:42,233
I took an oath to save lives.

404
00:20:42,367 --> 00:20:44,167
Even the lives
of my enemies.

405
00:20:46,933 --> 00:20:48,933
So why is it like this?

406
00:20:49,067 --> 00:20:53,033
Shouldn't you be thanking me
instead of getting mad?

407
00:20:53,167 --> 00:20:56,033
I saved Felma's life.

408
00:20:56,167 --> 00:20:57,733
Manuel...

409
00:20:57,867 --> 00:21:00,467
is all you ever see in me
pure evil?

410
00:21:02,933 --> 00:21:05,400
Open your eyes.

411
00:21:11,767 --> 00:21:12,967
Look, Mom.

412
00:21:13,100 --> 00:21:16,600
These are photos from
our trip together.

413
00:21:16,733 --> 00:21:18,067
We all looked so happy.

414
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:21,667
My shots look great.

415
00:21:21,800 --> 00:21:25,500
Yeah, I remember some of it...

416
00:21:25,633 --> 00:21:27,700
but only bits and pieces.

417
00:21:27,833 --> 00:21:31,167
I don't even remember
why we went on that trip.

418
00:21:32,500 --> 00:21:34,233
Well, Mom, we just decided
to go together.

419
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:38,600
Felma's brain is blocking
the painful memories.

420
00:21:40,033 --> 00:21:42,133
She even forgot that I left her.

421
00:21:43,100 --> 00:21:47,267
She doesn't remember Jessica,
either, or her death.

422
00:21:49,433 --> 00:21:51,567
So why does she remember Hazel?

423
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:56,433
Noah... Manuel?

424
00:21:56,567 --> 00:21:58,700
What are you two
whispering about?

425
00:22:01,267 --> 00:22:04,133
Felma, we were just wondering

426
00:22:04,267 --> 00:22:06,000
why you went to Hazel.

427
00:22:07,433 --> 00:22:09,167
I don't really know either.

428
00:22:10,533 --> 00:22:11,867
But maybe...

429
00:22:13,267 --> 00:22:14,967
it's because...

430
00:22:16,733 --> 00:22:18,133
she's my best friend?

431
00:22:18,267 --> 00:22:20,767
Hazel is not
your best friend, Felma.

432
00:22:23,333 --> 00:22:25,033
The doctor said...

433
00:22:25,167 --> 00:22:26,867
we shouldn't confuse her.

434
00:22:30,533 --> 00:22:34,267
But she treated
you well, right?

435
00:22:34,400 --> 00:22:35,733
Yes, Manuel.

436
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:40,933
She actually
saved me twice.

437
00:22:41,067 --> 00:22:42,767
When...

438
00:22:42,900 --> 00:22:45,067
I had a seizure...

439
00:22:46,467 --> 00:22:48,833
and when...

440
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:52,133
my head hurt so badly

441
00:22:52,267 --> 00:22:54,933
I thought I was going to die.

442
00:22:55,067 --> 00:22:58,000
Good thing she rushed me here.

443
00:23:00,667 --> 00:23:03,133
I owe her my life.

444
00:23:12,533 --> 00:23:13,800
What is it now, Manuel?

445
00:23:13,933 --> 00:23:15,500
What are you accusing me
of this time?

446
00:23:15,633 --> 00:23:17,000
Felma's looking for you.

447
00:23:17,133 --> 00:23:20,067
The swelling has progressed.
The tumor is aggressive.

448
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:21,967
And we still don't know
if it's cancerous,

449
00:23:22,133 --> 00:23:24,367
so we need to remove it
as soon as possible.

450
00:23:25,333 --> 00:23:26,700
Excuse me.

451
00:23:27,633 --> 00:23:28,900
Friend,

452
00:23:29,033 --> 00:23:31,600
if I may suggest,
you should have the surgery now.

453
00:23:31,733 --> 00:23:34,133
Are you seriously wishing
for Felma to die?

454
00:23:34,267 --> 00:23:37,633
Whether I wish it or not,
it's going to happen.

455
00:23:37,767 --> 00:23:41,233
Now let's make that
dream a reality.

456
00:23:41,367 --> 00:23:42,700
Hazel?
